    "created_at": "2026-01-06T06:46:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-01-06T06:46:52Z",
    "body": "> > Please try setting `directory.truncate_to_repo` to `false`.\n> \n> This worked great to bring it from 72ms -> 1ms, why is this?\n\nWhen `truncate_to_repo` is set, starship checks to see if it's in a git repo. If it is, it changes the directory it shows to start at the root of that repo.\n\nBut since it checks git, it's slow (according to this issue). Turning off `truncate_to_repo` means it never touches git, and it's fast again.",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
