    "updated_at": "2026-03-09T06:45:59Z",
    "body": "> I met the same issue, but setting directory.truncate_to_repo to false does not work. Removeing all $git_branch$git_status$git_state in format works, but it disables git function in starship completely.\n\nI believe the git status is cached after the first time it runs. So it's less \"directory is slow\" and more \"the first git thing that starship does is slow\".\n\nWhich yeah, means you have to disable all of the git functionality to get past this :(\n\n",
    "author_association": "NONE",
